        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1979-11-21T06:45:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1979-11-21T06:45:00-05:00" n="380"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d380">
                <head>380. Telegram From the Consulate in Karachi to the Department of State<note
                        n="1" type="source" xml:id="d380fn1">Source: National Archives, <gloss
                            target="#t_RG_1">RG</gloss> 59, Central Foreign Policy File,
                        D790537–0262. Confidential; Flash.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Karachi</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1979-11-21T11:45:00+00:00">November 21, 1979, 1145Z</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6612. Subject: Anti-US Demonstrations in Pakistan—3.</p>
                <p>1. Our contact in Islamabad reports that group in Embassy vault area are becoming
                    concerned about supply of oxygen in vault. Contact <pb facs="0909" n="864"
                        xml:id="pg_864"/> reports British Ambassador has been in touch with
                    President Zia and reports no rpt no concrete result.<note n="2" xml:id="d380fn2"
                        >See <ref target="#d383">Document 383</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>2. If Department could establish contact with Zia either directly or indirectly
                    through Embassy Washington, that might help to spur on what appears to our
                    observers in Islamabad to be sluggish <gloss target="#t_GOP_1">GOP</gloss>
                    response to Embassy take-over by mob. We are trying our best through our
                    contacts but so far aside from report of helicopter on roof our efforts have not
                    been crowned with success.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="strong">Post</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
